observations.recommendation:
We recommended that:

a.)  the Local Chief Executive require the Budget Officer and the Municipal Accountant to refrain from utilizing the LDRRMF to purposes not related to disaster risk management activities;

b.) the LDRRMO and Municipal Accountant submit monthly report on the receipt and utilization of LDRRMF to the concerned offices for proper monitoring and control; 

c.) ledger cards be required for the supplies, materials, equipment and relief goods donated or procured out of the fund.

We recommended that:

a.)  the Local Chief Executive to continue to ensure that proper segregation, collection, transport, storage, treatment and disposal of solid waste through the formulation and adoption of the best environmental practices in ecological waste management are observed;

b.) prohibit the construction/maintenance of any form of waste disposal facility due to the critical status of its location which is within the Pantabangan-Carranglan, Watershed Reservation protected area under Presidential Proclamation 561 of 1969;

c.) prohibit the construction or operation of landfills or any waste disposal facility on any aquifer, groundwater reservoir watershed area or any portion thereof as required in Section 48 of RA No. 9003; and

d.) provide sufficient budget to finance hauling of residual waste for dumping in sanitary landfill outside the locality.

