We recommended that the Local Chief Executive to continue to:
(a) ensure that proper segregation, collection, transport, storage, treatment and disposal of solid waste through the formulation and adoption of the best environmental practices in ecological waste management are observed;
(b)  prohibit the construction/maintenance of any form of waste disposal facility due to the critical status of its location which is within the Pantabangan-Carranglan, Watershed Reservation protected area under Presidential Proclamation 561 of 1969;
(c)  prohibit the construction or operation of landfills or any waste disposal facility on any aquifer, groundwater reservoir watershed area or any portion thereof as required in Section 48 of RA No. 9003; and
(d) provide sufficient budget to finance hauling of residual waste for dumping in sanitary landfill outside the locality.

We recommended that and the Management agreed that the Local Chief Executive strictly observe the provisions of COA Circular No. 97-002 in the granting of cash advances. Extra effort should be exerted for the immediate settlement/liquidation of the cash advances especially those granted to elected officials.  If liquidation could not be made, the following remedial measures may be resorted to as follows:

Withhold the salaries and/or other benefits as provided for under           Section 5.1.3 of COA Circular No. 97-002 and/or;


Appropriate administrative actions against the official/employee who failed to liquidate their cash advances;

Refrain from granting of additional cash advances to official/employee unless their previous cash advances were liquidated and limit the grant of cash advance to elected officials only for their travelling expenses and allowances; and

We recommended that management:

strictly adhere with the provisions of the NGAS Manual and related COA Circulars in the custody and management of government properties. Conduct physical inventory of government properties regularly and update/prepare the required reports of serviceable and unserviceable properties; 

maintain complete subsidiary records and Property Card to facilitate periodic reconciliation of the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment with the books of accounts;

revisit the guidelines to correct Estimated Useful Life of each PPE and effect the necessary correction on the depreciation provided for each PPE; and

efficiently adhere with the requirements of the NGAS in the issuance of PPE. Each item of the PPE should be evidenced with Property Acknowledgment Receipt and be renewed every three (3) years thereafter.
